.sh 3 "ASP Active Procedures"
.lp
This \fI\)Load Grouping\fR extension supplements the ASP Active Procedures as
follows:
.lp
When an ASP sends an \fB\)ASPAC\fR message to activate the ASP within an
Application Server, the ASP \fB\)MAY\fR choose to activate within a \fI\)Load
Group\fR for the specified AS by including the \fI\)Load Selection\fR
parameter in the \fB)ASPAC\fR message.
.lp
When an SGP receives an \fB\)ASPAC\fR message with a \fI\)Load Selection\fR
parameter in the message, or where the SGP is otherwise configured to activate
the ASP in a configured \fI\)Load Group\fR, when the SGP moves the ASP to the
ASP-ACTIVE state for the AS, it also moves the ASP to the ASP-ACTIVE state for
the \fI\)Load Group\fR identified by the \fI\)Load Selector\fR field in the
\fI\)Load Selection\fR parameter.  In either case, if the activation is
successful, the SGP includes the \fI\)Load Selection\fR parameter in the
\fB\)ASPAC ACK\fR message.
.lp
If the \fI\)Load Selector\fR in the \fB\)ASPAC\fR message is invalid, the SGP
responds with ERR("Error - Invalid Load Selector").  If the \fI\)Load
Selection\fR parameter is not present in the \fB\)ASPAC\fR message and the SGP
is configured to require one, or the \fI\)Load Selector\fR field is not valid
or unconfigured for the Application Server, the SGP responsds with ERR("Error
- Unsupported/Unconfigured/Missing Load Selector").  If the \fI\)Load
Selection\fR parameter contains an invalid or unsupported \fI\)Load
Distribution\fR value, or the \fI\)Load Selection\fR parameter is missing but
the SGP cannot determine the distribution applicable to the \fI\)Load Group\fR
without one, the SGP response with ERR("Error - Invalid/Unsupported/Missing
Load Distribution").
.lp
There are three modes of Application Server traffic handling in the SGP at the
Application Server level and three modes of AS traffic handling at the Load
Group level: Override, Loadshare and Broadcast.  When included, the
\fI\)Traffic Mode Type\fR parameter in the \fB\)ASPAC\fR message indicates the
traffic handling mode to be used in a particular Application Server between
Load Groups.  When included, the \fI\)Load Distribution\fR field in the
\fI\)Load Selection\fR parameter indicates the traffic handling mode to be
used between ASPs within a Load Group.
.lp
In the case of an Override mode AS, reception of an ASP Active message at an
SGP may move a \fI\)Load Group\fR to the LG-ACTIVE state.  When an LG moves
to the LG-ACTIVE state in an Override mode AS, this causes the (re)direction
of all traffic for the AS to the active Load Group.
Distribution of traffic within the Load Group is determine on the basis of the
Load Distribution mode of the Load Group.
Any previously active Load Group is now considered to be in state LG-INACTIVE
and \fB\)SHOULD\fR no longer receive traffic from the SGP within the AS.
The SGP then \fB\)MUST\fR send a Notify message ("Alternate ASP Active") and
include the \fI\)Load Selection\fR parameter in the Notify message indicating
the \fI\)Load Group\fR that has become active.
.lp
In the case of a Loadshare mode AS, the reception of an ASP Active message at
an SGP that moves a \fI\)Load Group\fR to the LG-ACTIVE state causes the
direction of specific traffic flows associated with the \fI\)Load Selector\fR
to the \fI\)Load Group\fR.  The assignment of traffic flows to \fB\)Load
Selector\fR values is implementation depenedent, but could be based on
specific information in the protocol data message.
.lp
In the case of a Broadcast mode AS, reception of an ASP Active message at an
SGP that results in moving a \fI\)Load Group\fR to the LG-ACTIVE state within
the AS causes the direction of traffic to the newly active \fI\)Load Group\fR
in addition to all the other LGs that are currently active for the AS.  The
algorithm at the SGP for broadcasting traffic within an AS to all the active
ASPs is a simple broadcast algorithm, where every message is sent to each of
the active Load Groups.
.sh 3 "ASP Inactive Procedures"
.lp
This \fI\)Load Grouping\fR extension supplements the ASP Active procedures of
the UAs as follows:
.lp
When an ASP wishes to withdraw from a specific \fI\)Load Group\fR within an
Application Server, the ASP sends an ASP Inactive message to the SGP with a
\fI\)Load Selection\fR parameter included in the message.  In the case where
the ASP does not include the \fI\)Load Selection\fR parameter in the ASP
Inactive message, the SGP must know via configuration data which Load Groups
the ASP is a member.  Upon receiving an ASP Inactive message with included
or implied \fI\)Load Selection(s)\fR, the SGP moves the ASP to the
ASP-INACTIVE state in each of the Load Groups indicated.
.lp
