.sh 2 "Registration"
.lp
UAs permit Application Server Processes to register for the Routing Context
(Interface Identifier) associated with a Routing Key (Link Key).  This draft
extends the registration procedure to also permit the Application Server
Process to register for a \fI\)Load Group\fR identifier in addition to the
Routing Contex/Interface Id.  This is performed using a \fI\)Load Group\fR which
has the same form as the Routing Key, but has some additional fields which are
only applicable to Loadsharing.
.lp
In addition to the normal registration procedures of the UAs, the following
additional error conditions can occur:
.ip "\fI""Error - Invalid Load Group""\fR"
This error \fB\)MUST\fR be sent in an \fI\)Error (ERR)\fR message if the SG
determines that the Load Group is invalid.
.ip "\fI""Error - Unsupported/Unconfigured Load Group""\fR"
This error \fB\)MUST\fR be sent in an \fI\)Error (ERR)\fR message whenever the
SG determines that the Load Group provided in a \fI\)REG REQ\fR message has
not be configured and the SG does not support dynamic allocation of Load
Selectors for the specified Key, and \fB\)MUST\fR be sent in an \fI\)Error
(ERR)\fR message whenever the SG determines that the Load Group provided in
a \fI\)REG REQ\fR message is not supported by the SG.
.ip "\fI""Error - Invalid/Unsupported/Missing Load Distribution""\fR"
This error \fB\)MUST\fR be sent in an \fI\)Error (ERR)\fR message whenever the
SG determines that the Load Distribution associated wtih a Load Group is
invalid, is not supported by the SG, or is required to determine the Load
Distribution algorithm of the \fI\)Load Group\fR but is missing from
the Load Group in the \fI\)REG REQ\fR message.
.sh 2 "ASP Activation"
.lp
When activating, this draft extends the UA activation procedures by permitting
an optional \fI\)Load Selection\fR parameter to be included in the ASP Active
(ASPAC) and ASP Active Ack (ASPAC ACK) messages.  The \fI\)Load Selection\fR
parameter is used to indicate for which \fI\)Load Group\fR the
concerned Application Server is becoming active.
.lp
Whenever the SG is unable to activate the ASP within the selected Application
Server \fI\)Load Group\fR, the SG \fB\)MUST\fR reply with an
\fI\)Error (ERR)\fR message containing one of the errors defined in the UA
documents\*(#u, or one of the following additional errors:
.ip "\fI""Error - Invalid Load Group Identifier""\fR"
.sh 2 "ASP Deactivation"
.lp
